RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intellectualism
<hw>In`tel*lec"tu*al*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Intellectual power; intellectuality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The doctrine that knowledge is derived from pure
reason.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Preference for activities involving exercise of the
intellect;</def> <specif>sometimes,</specif> <def>an excessive emphasis
on abstract or intellectual matters with deprecation of the value of
feelings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intellectualist</ent>⟦br⟧
